article.headline: Houston 97, UCF 69
article.story: ORLANDO, Fla. -- Aubrey Coleman notched a double-double, scoring 30 points and grabbing 10 boards, to help Houston rout Central Florida 97-69 on Wednesday night. Coleman was one of four Cougars (13-7, 4-3 Conference USA) in double figure scoring, as Qa'rraan Calhoun had 18, Kelvin Lewis 17 and Marcus Cousin 10. Calhoun was also 3-for-3 from beyond the arc, dished out three assists and tallied two blocks. Coleman added five assists and three steals. Jermaine Taylor led the Knights (15-7, 5-3) with 26 points, while Tony Davis scored 20 and grabbed 13 rebounds. The Cougars led by as many as 20 points in the first half, and were up 43-28 at halftime. Houston hit 26 of 28 free throws en route to victory compared to the Knights, who made just 13 of 20 from the line. It was the worst home loss for UCF since Ohio defeated them 94-66 on December 28, 1998.
